#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn9.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga "
msgstr "1. In the Woods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Nāgadattasutta "
msgstr "7. With Nāgadatta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.201, sc1
msgctxt "sn9.7:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā nāgadatto kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Nāgadatta was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.7:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā nāgadatto atikālena gāmaṃ pavisati, atidivā paṭikkamati. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Nāgadatta had been entering the village too early and returning late in the day. "

msgctxt "sn9.7:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā āyasmato nāgadattassa anukampikā atthakāmā āyasmantaṃ nāgadattaṃ saṃvejetukāmā yenāyasmā nāgadatto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ nāgadattaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the deity haunting that forest had compassion for Nāgadatta, wanting what’s best for him. So they approached him wanting to stir him up, and recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn9.7:2.1"
msgid "“Kāle pavisa nāgadatta, "
msgstr "“Entering too early, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.7:2.2"
msgid "Divā ca āgantvā ativelacārī; "
msgstr "and returning after spending too much of the day, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.7:2.3"
msgid "Saṃsaṭṭho gahaṭṭhehi, "
msgstr "Nāgadatta socializes with lay people, "

# NOTE: Following BB’s proposed readings.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.7:2.4"
msgid "Samānasukhadukkho. "
msgstr "sharing their joys and sorrows. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.433, sc3
msgctxt "sn9.7:3.1"
msgid "Bhāyāmi nāgadattaṃ suppagabbhaṃ, "
msgstr "I’m afraid for Nāgadatta; he’s so reckless "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.7:3.2"
msgid "Kulesu vinibaddhaṃ; "
msgstr "in his attachment to families. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.7:3.3"
msgid "Mā heva maccurañño balavato, "
msgstr "May he not come under the King of Death’s power, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vasaṃ upesī”ti → vasamesīti (bj, s1-3, km) | vasam eyyā ti (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn9.7:3.4"
msgid "Antakassa vasaṃ upesī”ti. "
msgstr "under the sway of the terminator!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn9.7:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā nāgadatto tāya devatāya saṃvejito saṃvegamāpādīti. "
msgstr "Impelled by that deity, Venerable Nāgadatta was struck with a sense of urgency."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
